Contents of directory contrib/porting
==========================================

1)      Name:		fix-comments.c
	Author:		Hans De Goede <hans@highrise.nl> 
	Description:   	A utility to patch original mame sources to xmame 
	Notes:		Convert c++ style comments to std-c style,
                        dos2unix text conversion, eof character
                        removal and lowercase #include's and fix \ to /.

2)	Name:		fix-mame
	Author:		Hans de Goede <hans@highrise.nl>
	Description:	A script which should be run from the root of a just
			unpacked msdos mame src tree, which does most
			of the nescesarry porting steps.
	Notes:		Also see porting.txt for a full description on how
			howto port a msdos src tree to unix.

3)	Name:		lowercase
	Author:		??
	Description:	A perl script which lowercases the contents of any
			textfiles given to it on the commandline.
	Notes:		This is no longer used in porting xmame

4)	Name:		porting.txt
	Author:		Hans de Goede
	Description:	A text file describing how to port the msdos src
			tree to unix.

5)	Name:		readme
	Author:		Hans de Goede <hans@highrise.nl>
	Description:	This file

6)	Name:		strip_
	Author:		jer johnson (jer@gweep.net)
	Description:	A perl script which remove the leading _ in front of
			symbols in nasm files, so that they work with elf
			based systems which don't use leading underscores.
